<h4>Number of people with mental and neurodevelopmental disorders</h4>
It's estimated that, globally, close to 950 million people have a mental or neurodevelopmental disorder (this is <a href="https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/number-with-mental-and-substance-use-disorders">over 1.1 billion</a> when substance use disorders are included). This split between males and females is similar, with an estimated 486 million females, and 462 million males in 2016. The relative under-reporting of these disorders means it's challenging to give a highly accurate measure of this change over time. Nonetheless, IHME estimates that this represents an increase from around 652 million in 1990.

You can view these statistics for any country using the "change country" function in the chart below.

